review_blob:
Very nice beer! Will rebuy for my collection. 
Very pleasant surprise. Try it!
I thought this was a very tasty blonde beer. Normally I dont like blonde beers too much!
OK beer but I have tasted better strong beers (Bush, EKU). Was a one-off try.
Good brown ale. However taste has a tendency to be a bit watery. I like it nonetheless.
OK beer but something is missing in the taste...  For a boutique brewery the beers of the brewery lack character.
Like all the beers of the Leffe range (OK, with exception of Leffe Ruby) this is a very good beer. I like its taste specially, one of my favourite beers!
Pretty good "Weissbier" albeit not best in the world. Some depth in the taste is missing but its not unpleasant!
For me the best brazilian lager beer. Also has as speciality many "sister" beers that are very good (niche beers)!
Pretty good dark beer. Could be better though (some sweetness missing vis-a-vis european dark beers).
I like this beer. Very nice belgian White Beer. I have this one always in my fridge..
Very watery beer. Taste is not unpleasant but just very very very light. There are definitely better beers in Brazil.
Typical "spanish" beer. Malty taste. Not bad but definitely not the most tasty beer in the world. But I would rebuy it!
On of the first beers that were not Lager available in Brazil. While definitely not one of the best black beers of the world its one of the best beers of Brazil.
